<section class="about-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">About Payxem</div>
    <h1 class="headline-lg">Getting Paid Should<br>Be Simple</h1>
    <p class="section-subtitle">
      Payxem launched in April 2026 to solve a problem thousands of freelancers know too well: getting paid internationally shouldn't require $150 minimum withdrawals or $30 annual fees.
    </p>
    <p class="section-subtitle" style="margin-top: 12px;">
      When you need to earn $150 before you can withdraw, a $50 project means waiting weeks or months to access your own money.
    </p>
    <p class="section-subtitle" style="margin-top: 16px;">
      If you're a freelancer, consultant, or small business owner in Pakistan, Bangladesh, or similar markets where PayPal doesn't operate, you've probably dealt with at least one of these:
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-section-inner">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Limited receiving &amp; withdrawal options</strong> — Major platforms force you to wait until you've earned $150 before you can access your money. For freelancers earning $50–200/month, that means waiting weeks.</li>
        <li><strong>Expensive annual fees</strong> — Paying $30/year just to receive payments eats into your income before you've even started.</li>
        <li><strong>Complex platforms</strong> — Most invoicing tools are built for large companies with finance teams. You just need to send an invoice and get paid.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="emphasis">Payxem was built to fix this.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

